<paragraph blockId="24.[120,749,1869,2011]" lastBlockId="24.[793,1422,151,323]" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[121,185,1869,1893]" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[197,376,1870,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis box="[197,376,1870,1893]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">Bama aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the palest general coloration of any 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[168,230,1899,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[168,230,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">Bama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[364,470,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grande">
<emphasis box="[364,470,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. grande</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The wing venation most resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[310,453,1928,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis box="[310,453,1928,1951]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but details of the aedeagus differ from that species and approach those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[601,740,1958,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis box="[601,740,1958,1981]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the absence of strong black setulae on the posteroventral margin of the sternopleuron, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1123,1269,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis box="[1123,1269,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[962,1107,182,205]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis box="[962,1107,182,205]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from most other species. The armature of the mid coxa, including the dense brush of coarse black setulae (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1180,239,264]" captionStart="Figures 39–41" captionStartId="23.[297,369,1593,1615]" captionTargetBox="[298,1328,148,1581]" captionTargetId="figure-138@23.[298,1335,136,1584]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 39–41. Bama aurantium n.sp. (39) Wing of female (Stony Logging Area).(40) Mid coxae, male.(41) Distal part of aedeagus (Upper Manki), scale = 0.2 mm.bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684909/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) is unique in the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[793,1422,151,323]" pageId="24" pageNumber="48">The specific epithet is a noun in botanical Latin—an orange, in reference to the coloration of the thorax.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
